FT  04 JUN 94 / London Stock Exchange: Equity Futures and Options Trading
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TERRY BYLAND
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Derivatives markets continued to give good support to the recovery in the
underlying equity market, writes Terry Byland. Trading volume in the June
contract on the Footsie had jumped to more than 23,000 contracts in late
trading last night. However, the discount of the contract to the cash
market, which had been cut to four points in official trading hours, widened
to nearly 10 points in later deals.
Progress was erratic, however, with the discount narrowing at first but
widening later as investors reacted nervously to trends in US bond markets.
