<HEADLINE>
FT  04 JUN 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
During the week prices of both black and white pepper went up drastically,
reports Man-Producten. Improving demand from American buyers for larger
quantities sent up prices in India and Indonesia immediately which indicates
how thin the market is these days. In the US market spot black pepper
improved to about USDollars 85/lb and in Europe the grade 1 went up to about
USDollars 1,750. The white pepper price went up to about USDollars 2,950
spot and nearby shipment positions. Since the new crop white pepper can only
be expected as from August onwards and spot stocks in Europe and the USA are
really small we might expect still higher levels.
