<HEADLINE>
FT  04 JUN 94 / Record price paid for Victorian art
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A portrait by the Victorian painter William Holman Hunt of his son Hilary
sold for Pounds 969,500 at Christie's yesterday, a record for this
Pre-Raphaelite artist. The previous best was Pounds 48,000 paid in 1973.
At Christie's South Kensington 'African Children' by David Sheppard,
depicting two young zebra, sold for Pounds 110,000 - a record for this
artist - at Christie's first sale devoted exclusively to wildlife art.
