<HEADLINE>
FT  03 JUN 94 / World Stock Markets: Venezeula
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Equities in Caracas recorded their fifth consecutive rise as foreign
investors, particularly from the US, were seen buying heavily. The market
has been attracting overseas interest following the decision earlier this
week to replace a capital gains tax of up to 37 per cent with a 1 per cent
share transaction levy.
The Merinvest index climbed 11.49, or 8.2 per cent, to 150.80 in turnover
that was reported to be above Dollars 6m, compared with a recent average of
some Dollars 3m.
Caracas is one of the smallest of the Latin American markets, with a total
capitalisation of some Dollars 6bn, and, in dollar terms, has underperformed
the region in the IFC emerging markets index.
