FT  03 JUN 94 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The official Australian market indicator closed this week at 628 cents a
kg., 11 cents higher than a week before and at a new high for the season.
The market cannot however be described as outstandisgly buoyant. Finer
Merinoes were again in strong demand, and there were price increases
affecting other categories, but New Zealand was a cheaper market. An erratic
and uncertain market impression is not unusual towards the end of a selling
season, but it is making the task of passing on recent wool price rises to
retailers a good deal more difficult. For wool the rises in price has been
enhanced by currency changes, with the Australian dollar strong against the
US dollar as well as against sterling.
