<HEADLINE>
FT  03 JUN 94 / International Company News: Bridge urges shareholders to
reject bid
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Bridge Oil, the Australian oil and gas company which is the subject of a
ADollars 295m (USDollars 226.9m) unsolicited bid from Texas-based Parker &amp;
Parsley, said yesterday that independent valuations had suggested that
Bridge shares were worth between ADollars 0.95 and ADollars 1.13.
It noted that this was substantially higher than the current 70
cents-a-share cash offer from the US oil independent, and urged shareholders
to reject the bid.
'The offer is a blatantly opportunistic attempt to get you to sell your
shares at a price well below their true value,' commented Bridge directors.
</TEXT>
